Hi, we’re having trouble with integrating Choreo for autonomous with our CTRE Swerve Generator code. This is our first time using ChoreoLib as last year we used PathPlannerLib. We’re not using PathPlannerLib because it can’t read the Choreo file for some reason (any ideas?). Thus, we’re not sure why, but the sample path that we created to go from the center of the auton start zone to the red line of the reef isn’t being followed. It goes forward while turning a little bit and stops at an angle in front of the reef. Here’s our code. Any help would be appreciated!

What is the path that you’re trying to run called? Looks like “New Path” is the right one, so that’s set up correctly.

One thing I notice is that your Autos class shouldn’t extend Command, because it isn’t a command. That’s not the problem here though.

Found it.

You’ve drawn a path on the red side of the field in Choreo, but you’re setting up your AutoFactory with alliance flipping set to true. Thus, when on red alliance, the path is mirrored to the blue side. You have two ways to fix this. The works-for-now way is to set alliance flipping to false, and the paths will always be on the side you drew them on. However, I recommend redrawing your test path on the blue side, and keeping the mirroring on.

Hello,
Thanks for looking into our code and finding an issue. We started by changing alliance flipping to false, saying that if it worked, we would redraw the path and set it to true. However, it went backwards while turning. Then, we tried using our somewhat-decent Limelight-based odometry during the path, which did the same thing, if not making it worse. Finally, we tried flipping the starting position by 180 degrees and went back to wheel odometry, which took us back to square one. Do you have any idea what is causing it to do this?
